The paper discusses neural network architectures with memory and attention mechanisms for question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes improvements to the memory and input modules of the dynamic memory network (DMN), which involves machine learning techniques and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results, which suggests that the authors may have used techniques from machine learning and statistical modeling, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the DMN to both textual and visual question answering, which involves neural networks and potentially deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
